nts. She reveals how contrary to popular misconceptions, the West German government attempted to maintain a humane, foreign labour system and the workers themselves made crucial, often defiant, decisions. Turkish Guest Workers in Germany identifies the Turkish guest worker program as a postwar phenomenon that has much to tell us about the development of Muslim minorities in Europe and Turkey’s ever-evolving relationship with the European Union.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aForeign workers, TurkishzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aTurkszGermanyxEconomic conditionsy20th century. 0aTurkszGermanyxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2018z978311060679940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751509640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487515096423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487515096.jpg  a978-3-11-060679-9  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK